---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>
			<h1>Peak Rock<br /> Communication Services</h1>

			<p>
				Thanks for visiting. This site is currently under construction, please check back later.
			</p>

			<section id="services" class="offerings">
				<h2>What I Offer</h2>

				<details>
					<summary>Customised Network Solutions</summary>
					<p>
						Every environment is unique, from farms to factories, houses to office blocks. I tailor
						solutions based on customers individual and unique needs. I can optimise and provide
						solutions for internet failovers, automatically switching to a secondary service if the
						main one goes down, as well as provide the best recommendations for reliable service, and
						implementation of the structure on your property.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Existing network testing and auditing</summary>
					<p>
						Whatever infrastructure and documentation is in place, as things grow and get added over
						time, stuff changes and that can lead to problems. Testing and auditing existing
						infrastructure is a part of every survey, including documentation, leaving you with a
						product you can trust to be reliable.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Problem Solving</summary>
					<p>
						Whatever the problem is, there is a solution. I offer a bespoke service to engineer your
						network so that problems are considered in advance, ensuring reliability throughout the life
						of the installation. I don't offer a quick fix 24-7 call out service, I can't be in the
						highlands of Scotland, working on unknown stuff the instant something has gone wrong (sorry
						if that's you right now). But I do offer a long term solution, and support by process of
						surveying and implementing the required standards for a solid infrastructure.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>CCTV</summary>
					<p>
						Wired CCTV systems benefit from the highest standard of cabling. Errors happen when renewing
						a system and utilising existing cabling, and this compounds over time. In most cases I
						recommend a proper structured cabling solution, because it provides the most reliability and
						longevity.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>POS</summary>
					<p>
						I've lost count of the number of shops I've helped out whilst popping in to by milk because
						the card machine is down. POS cabling is fundamentally simple, but too often poorly
						implemented. I offer solutions to shops of all sizes to eliminate the normal problems that
						you'll know about if you're reading this.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>121 Service</summary>
					<p>
						I can work with you to design, build and implement systems for you and your exact needs, not
						by a company policy and not by affiliate requirements. Should you choose to utilise my
						services, you will only ever need to deal with me directly.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>WiFi Solutions</summary>
					<p>
						Whether you live in a castle or a flat, maintain an Airbnb, glamping site, or a farm, WiFi
						is one of those things we all want to just work - but seemingly never meets expectations. I
						have experience in everything from stadiums and large caravan parks down to bedsits in very
						crowded environment. The key is understanding the network requirement, not always relying on
						plug and play solutions.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Structured Cabling</summary>
					<p>
						I attained CCNI (certified network cable installer) and an NVQ Level 3 in Network
						Infrastructure / Cabling in 2018. Since then I have worked in some of the biggest networked
						buildings in the world (ask me about it). Ultimately, those wires that carry the internet
						about aren't just a jungle, space ship wiring or rat's nest, nor should they be. There are
						no regulations - and that leads to confusion, but there are meticulous standards. When
						they're followed, these systems become very easy to understand for anyone who has to maintain
						or use them. I can install the highest quality ethernet infrastructure in your home or
						business, and provide documentation and instruction to make sure you get the best out of it.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>First Fix Consultancy</summary>
					<p>
						All too often people consider the network only after they've completed the build. The
						plaster is on, the painter is in, all the plug sockets are right where they're wanted, but
						the TV doesn't work in the annex, and the office doesn't have any connectivity at all. First
						Fix, I can provide a plan that can be implemented by myself, your own builder, or
						electrician. With all the considerations that your project deserves.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Final Fix and implementation</summary>
					<p>
						Final fix and implementation ensures everything is completed, tested, labelled and working
						as expected before handover. This includes termination, validation, and making sure the
						system is reliable in real use.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>PBX / Phone Systems</summary>
					<p>
						Design and setup of practical phone systems suited to your environment, whether upgrading or
						starting fresh.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Guest WiFi Networks</summary>
					<p>
						Simple and secure guest access solutions that don’t compromise your main network.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Internet Failover & Backup Connectivity</summary>
					<p>
						Backup connectivity solutions to keep your network online when your main connection fails.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Starlink & 4G/5G Installations</summary>
					<p>
						Alternative connectivity setups for rural, mobile, or hard-to-reach locations.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Outbuilding & Multi-Building Connectivity</summary>
					<p>
						Reliable connections between buildings, annexes, workshops and external spaces.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Smart Devices & IoT Networking</summary>
					<p>
						Network setups that properly support smart devices and growing connected environments.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Remote Access & Monitoring Setup</summary>
					<p>
						Secure remote access and visibility into your network for easier management and support.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Hospitality & Airbnb Networking</summary>
					<p>
						Network design suited for guest environments where reliability and simplicity matter.
					</p>
				</details>

				<details>
					<summary>Network Documentation & Handover</summary>
					<p>
						Clear documentation so your system is understandable, maintainable, and future-proof.
					</p>
				</details>
			</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 100%;
		padding: 2rem 2rem 6rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.offerings {
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 4rem auto 0;
		text-align: left;
	}

	.offerings h2 {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 2.2rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.offerings details {
		border: 1px solid #ccc;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: white;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.offerings summary {
		cursor: pointer;
		padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.offerings summary::after {
		content: "+";
		float: right;
	}

	.offerings details[open] summary::after {
		content: "−";
	}

	.offerings details p {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		text-align: left;
	}
</style>